The paper discusses the design of mechanisms for various optimization problems, which are typically studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT) and involve combinatorial structures (cs.DS). The use of approximation algorithms and relaxation and rounding techniques suggests a connection to algorithms and complexity theory (cs.AI), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG).
